name: Itzamná - Mayan Idol
description:
This is one of the most important gods of the Mayan Gods. He is often depicted as a toothless old man with a large nose. There are many stories and myths about him since he was considered a cultural hero, because of his contributions to the cultivation of corn, the creation of calendars, and the discovery of Maya medicine.
The god Itzamná is the symbol that represents wisdom as well as the teaching of knowledge
